comments[19]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T19:24:59.262Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: actively shrinking the enforced CLI/MCP private-core baseline through the pm-3mna schema ownership extraction. This run will not claim the capstone complete unless the baseline truly reaches zero."
  "2026-07-14T19:41:00.327Z",codex-gpt5,"Progress evidence: removed all 17 schema-domain private-core edges previously attributed to src/cli/commands/schema.ts. The boundary ratchet passes with zero new imports; the broader baseline remains intentionally open and is not claimed complete."
  "2026-07-14T20:19:49.227Z",codex-root,"Final branch evidence: removed all 17 private-core imports formerly owned by src/cli/commands/schema.ts and deleted that stale baseline block. pnpm quality:static passes with no new private imports, no stale baseline entries, zero unsupported dynamic imports, 100% docstrings, and token budgets green. The repository-wide boundary baseline is not yet zero, so this capstone returns to open for the remaining command families."
  "2026-07-14T22:56:38.841Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-15: actively removing config/profile/init baseline entries as part of pm-3mna. This capstone will close only if the full repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise exact progress will be recorded and it will return to open."
  "2026-07-14T23:31:17.495Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence 2026-07-15: moved config, profile, init, init-agent-guidance, and templates into SDK ownership and removed their 54 grandfathered CLI-to-core edges. The static boundary gate reports actual_edge_count=642, baseline_edge_count=642, zero new imports, zero stale entries, and zero unsupported dynamic imports. Because 642 edges remain and the acceptance criterion requires zero plus deletion of the baseline, this capstone is deliberately returning to open rather than being falsely closed."
  "2026-07-15T01:03:56.201Z",codex-root,"Review-driven implementation evidence 2026-07-15: promoted the complete extension lifecycle engine and cohesive helpers from src/cli/commands/extension* into src/sdk/extension*, kept only thin CLI compatibility re-exports, and made SDK runtime/init consume the SDK implementation directly. This removed 45 additional grandfathered private-core edges: static quality reports actual_edge_count=597, baseline_edge_count=597, zero new/stale/dynamic violations. Suppression pruning reduced the mandatory budget 170 -> 167. Final all-source verification passes 291 files / 5,713 tests at exact 100%: 36,940 statements, 26,521 branches, 7,450 functions, 36,055 lines. The capstone remains incomplete because 597 edges remain, so it is returning to open."
  "2026-07-15T01:25:55.511Z",codex-root,"Second-head CodeQL evidence: accepted the polynomial-regex finding introduced by relocating the extension helper into the PR diff. Replaced the overlapping anchored alternation with two linear anchored trims and added a 20,004-character adversarial hyphen-run regression. Focused extension tests pass 125/125; strict lint/static quality pass; final all-source coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,713 tests. Thread reacted to, replied inline, and resolved."
  "2026-07-15T02:24:58.381Z",codex-root,"Third-head review evidence: replaced per-destination extension install locking with one scope-wide transaction lock carrying a UUID owner token; stale and final cleanup re-read ownership before removal, and regressions prove cross-destination serialization, invalid/stale-owner refusal, replacement-owner preservation, and owner-write cleanup. Install activation now requires explicit runtime status ok. Executable aliases moved into SDK contracts so SDK scaffolding has no reverse CLI dependency. Directory normalization uses linear index scans, eliminating both CodeQL regex findings. Focused extension/bootstrap tests pass 216/216; repository verification passes 291 files / 5,717 tests at exact 100%: 36,962 statements, 26,531 branches, 7,453 functions, 36,077 lines. Typecheck, lint, duplicates, static/docstring/package/token gates pass; suppression budget improved 167 -> 166. Temp-directory package-first dogfood passed 88 real CLI/SDK/package commands."
  "2026-07-15T03:10:16.485Z",codex-root,"Fourth-head CodeRabbit evidence: accepted the active-lock-expiry finding. Scope locks now run an owner-token-bound lease heartbeat at one-third of the stale interval; every tick re-reads current ownership before refreshing mtime, stop is an async barrier before final release, and heartbeat I/O failure remains best-effort without aborting the install. Regressions prove a transaction running beyond stale_ms retains exclusivity, replacement owners are never heartbeated or removed, and failed heartbeats do not break installs. Focused extension tests pass 124/124; full verification passes 291 files / 5,719 tests at exact 100%: 36,977 statements, 26,535 branches, 7,458 functions, 36,092 lines. Typecheck, strict quality gates, and 88-command temp-directory dogfood pass."
  "2026-07-15T06:48:50.369Z",codex-root,"Implementation scope 2026-07-15: actively remove governance/health/gc CLI-to-core allowances through SDK ownership. This capstone closes only if the complete repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise it will return to open with exact remaining-edge evidence."
  "2026-07-15T07:26:14.575Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence: this bundle removes the CLI-owned validate/health/gc implementations and 59 private import edges from the ratchet. The allowed baseline is now 62 entries, so the zero-baseline capstone is intentionally not closed; static quality proves no new reverse edges."
  "2026-07-15T20:21:24.960Z",codex-root-20260715,"Implementation scope 2026-07-15: actively remove execution/diagnostics CLI-to-core allowances through SDK ownership. This capstone closes only if the full repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise it returns to open with exact remaining-edge evidence."
  "2026-07-15T21:08:50.199Z",codex-root-20260715,"Progress evidence 2026-07-15: execution/diagnostics promotion removes 8 remaining CLI implementation files and 72 grandfathered private-core edges. The ratchet now reports 54 source files and 466 edges, with zero new imports, zero stale baseline entries, and zero unsupported dynamic imports. Full verification passes 293 files / 5,741 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 and strict static quality passes. Because the acceptance criterion requires a zero-entry baseline and deletion of the baseline file, this capstone is deliberately returning to open rather than being falsely closed."
  "2026-07-15T22:12:13.708Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Review-head evidence 2026-07-16: addressed every valid first-round Greptile and CodeRabbit finding before the second head. SDK telemetry now honors global.path and reports queue_drained only after a complete flush; eval preserves non-ENOENT filesystem failures; batch deduplication reuses the real execution outcome; linked-test timeouts require positive finite integers; regex assertions execute with a 100ms VM bound; background runs honor global author/noExtensions; and test-runs lifecycle operations are native SDK runtime actions. Added complete diagnostics docstrings and durable SDK documentation. Verification: 293 files / 5,747 tests pass at exact 100% (37,271 statements, 26,545 branches, 7,549 functions, 36,374 lines); typecheck, ESLint, zero-duplicate jscpd, 100% source/export/member docstrings, package boundary, token budgets, contracts, docs links, and tracked-file secret scanning all pass. Boundary ratchet remains 54 source files / 466 edges, so this capstone correctly returns to open."
  "2026-07-15T22:23:30.704Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Local Greptile review 411cf305-6dd5-44bb-b874-933a418079db identified one public-contract ergonomics gap: EvalSearchRunner exposed EvalSearchMode without a named SDK re-export. Accepted and fixed by re-exporting EvalSearchMode from sdk/eval; focused eval tests pass 16/16 and the complete package/example typecheck passes."
  "2026-07-15T22:38:32.201Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Committed-diff Greptile review ee8717e3-18e3-411e-abb0-e96c0c11352d identified inconsistent runId placement and a leaked test-runs SDK mock. Accepted both: every dedicated test-runs lifecycle action now accepts runId from either top-level action arguments or nested options, regression assertions prove both paths for status/logs/stop/resume, and teardown explicitly un-mocks the SDK module. Focused MCP tests pass 7/7, strict static quality passes, and full verification remains exact 100/100/100/100 across 293 files / 5,747 tests (37,271 statements, 26,553 branches, 7,549 functions, 36,374 lines)."
  "2026-07-15T23:06:07.430Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Second exact-head bot evidence: accepted Greptile thread 3591300444 and CodeRabbit thread 3591304225. Added native test-runs-start runtime dispatch plus a public TestRunsActionOptions union, explicitly narrowed each lifecycle branch, registered the start parameter contract, documented the complete durable lifecycle, and extended direct/MCP regressions. Verification: focused 37/37, contracts current, static/docstring/package/token gates green, and full coverage exact 100/100/100/100 across 293 files / 5,747 tests (37,274 statements, 26,555 branches, 7,550 functions, 36,377 lines)."
  "2026-07-15T23:25:17.080Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Final analyzer-head evidence 2026-07-16: DeepScan public defect 230757853 correctly identified a redundant maxBufferExceeded guard after the earlier terminal-state return; simplified the branch without behavior change. DeepSource's current dashboard run was configured as commonjs despite the checked-in module_system=es-modules contract, producing invalid ESM global findings; ESLint now explicitly declares module source type and disables the browser-script-only no-implicit-globals rule, while every tool-schema helper has substantive documentation. Verification passes: focused 225/225, typecheck, ESLint, zero-duplicate jscpd, contracts, 100% source/export/member docstrings, package boundary and token gates; full coverage is exact 100/100/100/100 across 293 files / 5,747 tests (37,274 statements, 26,555 branches, 7,550 functions, 36,377 lines). The boundary remains 54 source files / 466 edges, so this capstone returns to open."
  "2026-07-15T23:42:36.834Z",codex-sdk-platform,"Final exact-head Greptile evidence: accepted thread 3591372211. TestAllCommandOptions now carries the SDK invocation author into durable per-item test-all summaries, with a real PmClient regression proving sdk-test-all-author reaches appendTrackedTestRunSummary. Reacted and replied in the inline thread. Focused test-all passes 30/30; typecheck, contracts, static/docstring/package/token gates pass; full coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100 across 293 files / 5,748 tests (37,274 statements, 26,555 branches, 7,550 functions, 36,377 lines). The capstone remains open at 54 source files / 466 edges."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T06:21:39.876Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#565 progress (2026-07-15): 54 obsolete CLI-to-core import-boundary allowances removed; pm-3mna slice shipped (SDK owns config/profile/init/agent-guidance/templates/extension + createPmCliProgram + renderPmCommand). Baseline scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json still holds ~60 source files (commands/*, main.ts, register-*, mcp/server.ts) — the zero target remains. With 3mna/4a7m/hib1/zwpp shipped, remaining prerequisite slices are pm-oxrw (governance/health) then pm-oslr (execution/diagnostics)."
learnings[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T20:19:49.944Z",codex-root,Boundary burn-down is strongest when the implementation itself moves to an SDK-owned module; deleting a baseline block without changing ownership would only hide the dependency direction.
  "2026-07-14T23:31:18.238Z",codex-root,Compatibility shims must remain locally referenced or be deleted after SDK promotion; the orphan-module gate correctly prevents dead presentation paths from surviving solely for tests.
  "2026-07-15T02:24:59.166Z",codex-root,Shared extension managed-state and settings mutations require scope-level serialization; destination-level locks protect copies but cannot protect shared snapshots. Persisted unique ownership must be re-read before stale reclaim and final release so an earlier installer cannot delete a replacement lock.
  "2026-07-15T03:10:17.167Z",codex-root,"A stale timeout is a lease duration, not an install duration: long-running owners must refresh liveness under the same persisted owner token, and cleanup must await any in-flight heartbeat before comparing and releasing ownership."
